        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks GA for his article ["The daisy’s pedigree", <hi rend="italic">Cornhill Mag.</hi> 44 (1881): 168–81].</p> 
            <p>The evolutionary argument that petals are transformed stamens is "striking and apparently valid". Doubts petals are naturally yellow.</p>
            <p>Wallace’s "generalization about much modified parts being splendidly coloured" is also dubious except as both are caused by sexual selection.</p>
        </abstract>
